The Lawyers' Committee for Cultural Heritage Preservation (LCCHP) announces its third annual law student writing competition and welcomes papers of publishable quality that develop or present new or different perspectives on the law with respect to cultural heritage.  The deadline for submissions is June 14, 2007.  The first-place winner will receive a prize of $300 and the second-place winner will receive a prize of $200. Both winners will also be given assistance in publishing their works.

More information about the competition may be found at http://www.culturalheritagelaw.org/writingcompetition.html.


